Come on.
Let's go for a ride.

243
00:21:15.500 --> 00:21:18.875
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

244
00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:23.351
Rebecca:
<i>It's an old hunting cabin.</i>

245
00:21:23.375 --> 00:21:29.393
Hasn't been used in years.
but the water still runs.

246
00:21:29.417 --> 00:21:31.500
Whose is it?

247
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:33.893
Who do you think?

248
00:21:33.917 --> 00:21:39.518
Lucas:
<i>You really think your uncle</i>
<i>is gonna let me stay here?</i>

249
00:21:39.542 --> 00:21:41.792
He won't know.

250
00:21:44.917 --> 00:21:47.500
<i>How do you like it?</i>

251
00:21:50.792 --> 00:21:51.768
Yeah.

252
00:21:51.792 --> 00:21:54.667
<i>I thought you would.</i>

253
00:21:56.333 --> 00:21:58.625
No ghosts.

254
00:23:18.875 --> 00:23:22.583
( screams )

255
00:23:35.458 --> 00:23:39.083
( moaning )

256
00:23:58.083 --> 00:24:01.792
- Does this hurt?
- Not anymore.

257
00:24:02.750 --> 00:24:05.184
I hate that
they did this to you.

258
00:24:05.208 --> 00:24:10.142
I had been meaning to get
that tattoo removed anyway.

259
00:24:10.166 --> 00:24:11.434
( chuckles )

260
00:24:11.458 --> 00:24:14.834
Just wish it could
always be like this.

261
00:24:16.001 --> 00:24:18.001
Maybe one day.

262
00:24:21.208 --> 00:24:23.750
You okay?

263
00:24:25.583 --> 00:24:28.083
No.

264
00:24:29.583 --> 00:24:31.959
( sighs )

265
00:24:42.500 --> 00:24:46.792
Hang on right there.
He'll be with you
in a moment.

266
00:24:49.709 --> 00:24:51.625
You fuck.

267
00:24:55.709 --> 00:24:58.768
We have a strict agreement
with the Redbones.

268
00:24:58.792 --> 00:25:02.059
You keep your business
on the reservation

269
00:25:02.083 --> 00:25:04.685
and we keep ours off it.

270
00:25:04.709 --> 00:25:09.000
You are in breach
of that agreement.

271
00:25:21.166 --> 00:25:23.935
<i>( phone buzzing )</i>

272
00:25:23.959 --> 00:25:26.917
Yeah?

273
00:25:30.041 --> 00:25:33.601
I just got to work.
for fuck's sake.

274
00:25:33.625 --> 00:25:36.250
Who's there?

275
00:25:37.917 --> 00:25:38.976
Shit.

276
00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:42.726
No. Okay.
Don't do a fucking thing.

277
00:25:42.750 --> 00:25:44.184
I'm coming back to town.

278
00:25:44.208 --> 00:25:46.184
Man:
<i>Well. you can</i>
<i>ask him yourself.</i>

279
00:25:46.208 --> 00:25:49.142
<i>Things are going</i>
<i>fantastic over here.</i>

280
00:25:49.166 --> 00:25:51.559
This time you're buying.
Okay.

281
00:25:51.583 --> 00:25:53.142
All right. all right.
all right.

282
00:25:53.166 --> 00:25:56.041
Great.
Say hi to Carol for me.

283
00:25:57.125 --> 00:25:59.810
Hey there. Calvin.
What can I do you for?

284
00:25:59.834 --> 00:26:03.101
I'm not feeling great.
I'm gonna need to go home.

285
00:26:03.125 --> 00:26:05.267
- You look fine.
- I've got a stomach bug.

286
00:26:05.291 --> 00:26:07.601
I thought I could make it
through the day. but I can't.

287
00:26:07.625 --> 00:26:10.726
You're handling
the triquarterlies.
aren't you?

288
00:26:10.750 --> 00:26:13.583
- Mm-hmm.
- They done?

289
00:26:14.750 --> 00:26:16.226
Not yet. no.

290
00:26:16.250 --> 00:26:18.059
Kind of need those
done today.

291
00:26:18.083 --> 00:26:19.935
Well. I can take them
home with me

292
00:26:19.959 --> 00:26:22.685
and I'll have them
done for you first
thing tomorrow.

293
00:26:22.709 --> 00:26:26.875
We were late with them
last quarter. too.
weren't we?

294
00:26:27.291 --> 00:26:29.643
I don't think so. no.

295
00:26:29.667 --> 00:26:33.875
( echoes )
I think we were.
Calvin.

296
00:26:41.208 --> 00:26:44.333
( grunting )

297
00:26:47.125 --> 00:26:50.625
Gook motherfucker!

298
00:26:52.875 --> 00:26:54.959
( panting )

299
00:26:55.001 --> 00:26:57.083
( screams )

300
00:27:02.083 --> 00:27:05.184
I'll have those to you
first thing tomorrow.

301
00:27:05.208 --> 00:27:09.709
<i>( phones ringing )</i>

302
00:27:22.291 --> 00:27:24.625
<i>( door opens )</i>

303
00:27:27.333 --> 00:27:28.726
What the fuck
is he doing here?

304
00:27:28.750 --> 00:27:33.309
We came in and found him
here with this motherfucker
already in the vise.

305
00:27:33.333 --> 00:27:35.810
He was dealing
in our territory.

306
00:27:35.834 --> 00:27:41.017
The territory
you and your men are
charged with protecting.

307
00:27:41.041 --> 00:27:46.059
I brought him here
as a courtesy.

308
00:27:46.083 --> 00:27:47.267
Mm-hmm.

309
00:27:47.291 --> 00:27:50.226
So my tax dollars
aren't enough for you
and your little tribe. huh?

310
00:27:50.250 --> 00:27:54.726
Now you fuckers are going
to encroach on my business?

311
00:27:54.750 --> 00:27:57.375
Fuck you.

312
00:27:58.959 --> 00:28:00.935
I don't think so.

313
00:28:00.959 --> 00:28:02.267
We pay for your houses...

314
00:28:02.291 --> 00:28:06.309
- ( man groans )
- ...for your damn
reservations.

315
00:28:06.333 --> 00:28:08.726
for your school.
and your health care.

316
00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:12.393
even when all of you
were getting rich off
your fucking casinos. right?

317
00:28:12.417 --> 00:28:15.184
This country
has lost its spine.

318
00:28:15.208 --> 00:28:18.208
The politicians are
giving it away to the mutts
and the mongrels

319
00:28:18.250 --> 00:28:22.017
while good. pure-blooded
Americans go hungry.

320
00:28:22.041 --> 00:28:24.226
This isn't a nation anymore.

321
00:28:24.250 --> 00:28:26.768
It's a fucking soup kitchen.

322
00:28:26.792 --> 00:28:29.267
- And you know what?
- ( groans )

323
00:28:29.291 --> 00:28:31.142
We're all out
of fucking soup!

324
00:28:31.166 --> 00:28:35.125
- ( cracks )
- ( gurgles )

325
00:28:43.001 --> 00:28:44.101
Thanks for the heads up.

326
00:28:44.125 --> 00:28:46.351
You can tell Proctor
that we've got it
under control.

327
00:28:46.375 --> 00:28:51.041
Don't use his name
in front of outsiders.

328
00:28:51.083 --> 00:28:52.768
Him?

329
00:28:52.792 --> 00:28:57.500
Yeah. I don't think
he's paying too much
attention.

330
00:28:58.250 --> 00:29:00.750
( gurgling continues )

331
00:29:14.959 --> 00:29:18.250
You don't want me
to come back here.

332
00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:29.142
<i>( music playing )</i>

333
00:29:29.166 --> 00:29:32.041
<i>( door opens )</i>

334
00:29:34.375 --> 00:29:36.917
<i>( door closes )</i>

335
00:29:44.917 --> 00:29:47.208
Hey. Sugar.

336
00:29:50.250 --> 00:29:52.184
( scoffs )

337
00:29:52.208 --> 00:29:56.184
You disappear
for a year and a half...

338
00:29:56.208 --> 00:29:58.935
<i>you show up here</i>
<i>looking like...</i>

339
00:29:58.959 --> 00:30:01.226
<i>something</i>
<i>out of the Bible.</i>

340
00:30:01.250 --> 00:30:04.851
and all you got
to say for yourself is

341
00:30:04.875 --> 00:30:07.583
"Hey. Sugar"?

342
00:30:11.333 --> 00:30:13.333
How you been?

343
00:30:14.250 --> 00:30:19.166
Small talk?
Seriously?

344
00:30:21.333 --> 00:30:24.208
Somebody killed
Rebecca Bowman.

345
00:30:30.917 --> 00:30:33.309
I know that.

346
00:30:33.333 --> 00:30:36.893
Everybody around here
knows that.

347
00:30:36.917 --> 00:30:40.333
Now why do you
know that?

348
00:30:42.375 --> 00:30:44.935
Well...

349
00:30:44.959 --> 00:30:48.142
I guess I'm a suspect.

350
00:30:48.166 --> 00:30:51.434
Did you do it?

351
00:30:51.458 --> 00:30:54.142
No.

352
00:30:54.166 --> 00:30:57.184
Look.
it's a fair question.

353
00:30:57.208 --> 00:31:00.309
I mean.
look at yourself.

354
00:31:00.333 --> 00:31:03.351
Where the hell
have you been?

355
00:31:03.375 --> 00:31:06.226
I had to disappear
for a while.

356
00:31:06.250 --> 00:31:07.142
Clear my head.

357
00:31:07.166 --> 00:31:11.184
You clear your head
for a few days.

358
00:31:11.208 --> 00:31:12.434
A week maybe.

359
00:31:12.458 --> 00:31:16.017
For you.
maybe even a month.

360
00:31:16.041 --> 00:31:17.351
But you.
you went AWOL

361
00:31:17.375 --> 00:31:21.017
and you forgot
about your friends
and you forgot about...

362
00:31:21.041 --> 00:31:22.959
I didn't forget
about Job.

363
00:31:23.001 --> 00:31:27.500
How the fuck
was hiding away
gonna help him?

364
00:31:37.417 --> 00:31:40.625
You here
for your money?

365
00:31:41.917 --> 00:31:43.559
No.

366
00:31:43.583 --> 00:31:46.917
But I do need a car.

367
00:31:56.917 --> 00:31:57.935
Only thing I bought.

368
00:31:57.959 --> 00:32:03.500
Figured it might
come in handy if I ever
needed a quick exit.

369
00:32:07.417 --> 00:32:09.935
So what happens now?

370
00:32:09.959 --> 00:32:11.685
I don't know.

371
00:32:11.709 --> 00:32:14.935
But something. right?

372
00:32:14.959 --> 00:32:17.017
Yeah.

373
00:32:17.041 --> 00:32:19.393
Something.

374
00:32:19.417 --> 00:32:24.291
Remember. Hood.
you're not the sheriff
anymore.

375
00:32:26.041 --> 00:32:28.184
I never was.

376
00:32:28.208 --> 00:32:31.017
( engine starts )

377
00:32:31.041 --> 00:32:34.208
You know what I mean.

378
00:32:35.500 --> 00:32:39.709
<i>( chatter over P.A. )</i>

379
00:32:51.125 --> 00:32:54.434
( chuckles )
What'd the other guy
look like?

380
00:32:54.458 --> 00:32:56.101
Ha ha.

381
00:32:56.125 --> 00:32:59.000
Very fucking funny.

382
00:32:59.375 --> 00:33:01.726
Actually.
I wasn't kidding.

383
00:33:01.750 --> 00:33:05.291
( screaming )

384
00:33:07.667 --> 00:33:09.226
What did he look like?

385
00:33:09.250 --> 00:33:11.559
He looked like
a fucking asshole

386
00:33:11.583 --> 00:33:14.142
smashing the shit
out of my hands.

387
00:33:14.166 --> 00:33:18.184
The guy stuck around
long enough to walk
all over your face

388
00:33:18.208 --> 00:33:20.059
and you didn't even
get a look?

389
00:33:20.083 --> 00:33:22.726
It was dark.

390
00:33:22.750 --> 00:33:25.059
Don't worry.

391
00:33:25.083 --> 00:33:26.750
I got time.

392
00:34:08.166 --> 00:34:10.792
<i>( footsteps )</i>

393
00:34:14.375 --> 00:34:17.250
You're back.

394
00:34:24.375 --> 00:34:27.458
I'm sorry about
Rebecca.

395
00:34:28.542 --> 00:34:31.601
What does this
have to do with you?

396
00:34:31.625 --> 00:34:33.559
Nothing.

397
00:34:33.583 --> 00:34:34.810
And yet here you are.

398
00:34:34.834 --> 00:34:37.267
Is there anything
I should know?

399
00:34:37.291 --> 00:34:40.309
Your uncle.
he's not a good man.

400
00:34:40.333 --> 00:34:41.810
Well. then let me
live with you.

401
00:34:41.834 --> 00:34:43.309
I'm not
a good man either.

402
00:34:43.333 --> 00:34:46.101
I was gonna ask you
the same thing.

403
00:34:46.125 --> 00:34:48.142
You think I had anything
to do with my niece's death?

404
00:34:48.166 --> 00:34:51.142
You may not have killed her.
but you sure as shit
got her killed.

405
00:34:51.166 --> 00:34:56.208
As soon as you took her in.
it was only a matter of time.

406
00:34:57.166 --> 00:34:58.851
Yeah.

407
00:34:58.875 --> 00:35:01.750
You may be right.

408
00:35:02.333 --> 00:35:05.417
I'm gonna find
that son of a bitch.

409
00:35:06.208 --> 00:35:07.476
But as a mayor.

410
00:35:07.500 --> 00:35:13.458
I'm somewhat
hampered in my ability
to clarify matters.

411
00:35:14.583 --> 00:35:16.309
How'd you
pull that off?

412
00:35:16.333 --> 00:35:20.417
- I ran unopposed.
- Of course.

413
00:35:26.625 --> 00:35:28.601
Where would you start?

414
00:35:28.625 --> 00:35:31.875
The foothills.
The Boedickers.

415
00:35:31.917 --> 00:35:33.643
I heard they got
burned down.

416
00:35:33.667 --> 00:35:38.726
It's true.
but Aaron Boedicker
is still alive.

417
00:35:38.750 --> 00:35:42.393
You guys.
you did see the yellow
tape here. right?

418
00:35:42.417 --> 00:35:45.434
- Sheriff.
- It's fine.

419
00:35:45.458 --> 00:35:48.750
Our work is done here.

420
00:35:49.458 --> 00:35:50.726
You following me.
Brock?

421
00:35:50.750 --> 00:35:54.267
Me? No.
That's what
deputies are for.

422
00:35:54.291 --> 00:35:55.434
Is Hood a suspect?

423
00:35:55.458 --> 00:35:59.476
Well. if he was.
you'd be the first
to know it. wouldn't you?

424
00:35:59.500 --> 00:36:04.267
No. Mr. Hood
is a person of interest
in this case.

425
00:36:04.291 --> 00:36:07.375
which is something
you two have in common.

426
00:36:09.792 --> 00:36:11.351
Be careful. Sheriff.

427
00:36:11.375 --> 00:36:14.417
I always am.
Mr. Mayor.

428
00:36:19.458 --> 00:36:22.267
Just like
old times. huh?

429
00:36:22.291 --> 00:36:25.518
Except no one's bleeding.

430
00:36:25.542 --> 00:36:27.792
Yet.

431
00:36:38.709 --> 00:36:41.250
Hey. Kurt.

432
00:36:45.959 --> 00:36:50.458
Come on. bro.
How long you gonna
keep this up. man?

433
00:36:51.375 --> 00:36:53.226
Huh?

434
00:36:53.250 --> 00:36:54.476
I saved your
fucking life. Kurt.

435
00:36:54.500 --> 00:36:57.851
What do you think
Watts would have done?
He would have had you executed.

436
00:36:57.875 --> 00:37:00.768
I took action before
he could order it.
that's it.

437
00:37:00.792 --> 00:37:03.810
I was in the burn unit
for two months.

438
00:37:03.834 --> 00:37:05.434
I know
and I'm sorry.

439
00:37:05.458 --> 00:37:07.393
but you put me in
an impossible situation

440
00:37:07.417 --> 00:37:09.935
and I had to prove
my loyalty to the cause.

441
00:37:09.959 --> 00:37:12.208
You know that.

442
00:37:12.250 --> 00:37:14.559
Just come
for dinner. man.

443
00:37:14.583 --> 00:37:16.518
Maggie would really
love to see you.

444
00:37:16.542 --> 00:37:17.768
And we can
work this out.

445
00:37:17.792 --> 00:37:22.458
Brothers before Brotherhood.
that's what you always said.

446
00:37:24.000 --> 00:37:25.226
You're not my brother.

447
00:37:25.250 --> 00:37:29.625
What?
What the fuck did you
just say to me?

448
00:37:29.667 --> 00:37:33.434
I'm the only thing
standing between them
and you. asshole.

449
00:37:33.458 --> 00:37:37.750
You better fucking
remember that!

450
00:38:08.333 --> 00:38:11.309
<i>( car door opens )</i>

451
00:38:11.333 --> 00:38:13.643
<i>( door closes )</i>

452
00:38:13.667 --> 00:38:16.726
- Hey. Carrie.
- Hey. Brock.

453
00:38:16.750 --> 00:38:19.810
Wow. place is really
starting to come together.

454
00:38:19.834 --> 00:38:22.559
( laughs )
Thanks.

455
00:38:22.583 --> 00:38:25.917
No. looks good.

456
00:38:27.458 --> 00:38:28.518
How are the kids doing?

457
00:38:28.542 --> 00:38:33.625
Oh. you know.
Gordon's parents
are driving them crazy.

458
00:38:34.333 --> 00:38:37.000
Something on
your mind. Brock?

459
00:38:39.333 --> 00:38:44.351
Listen.
Carrie. I don't know
if you've heard. but...

460
00:38:44.375 --> 00:38:46.792
Hood is back.

461
00:38:48.959 --> 00:38:50.643
Guess you haven't heard.

462
00:38:50.667 --> 00:38:55.768
He's been living up
in the foothills
in a cabin.

463
00:38:55.792 --> 00:38:58.709
He... he looks rough.

464
00:39:01.458 --> 00:39:03.935
Just thought
you'd want to know.

465
00:39:03.959 --> 00:39:06.768
( clears throat )

466
00:39:06.792 --> 00:39:07.726
Yeah.

467
00:39:07.750 --> 00:39:09.959
Call me if you
need anything.
all right?

468
00:39:10.001 --> 00:39:13.333
Carrie:
Okay.

469
00:39:13.667 --> 00:39:18.001
- Have a good day.
- Thanks.

470
00:39:33.458 --> 00:39:36.125
<i>( silenced gunshot )</i>

471
00:39:39.959 --> 00:39:43.476
Lewis.
is everything okay?

472
00:39:43.500 --> 00:39:46.166
Lewis. come in.

473
00:39:53.875 --> 00:39:55.834
Don't fucking move.

474
00:39:57.500 --> 00:39:59.643
( chuckles )

475
00:39:59.667 --> 00:40:01.726
Something funny?

476
00:40:01.750 --> 00:40:03.726
Wait for it.

477
00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:06.709
<i>( silenced gunshot )</i>

478
00:40:38.500 --> 00:40:40.583
Lucas:
<i>Uh-uh.</i>

479
00:40:40.625 --> 00:40:43.125
Drop it!

480
00:40:49.000 --> 00:40:50.518
You.

481
00:40:50.542 --> 00:40:53.142
Me.

482
00:40:53.166 --> 00:40:55.166
Long time. huh?

483
00:40:57.667 --> 00:40:59.184
Why don't you
take a seat?

484
00:40:59.208 --> 00:41:04.208
You finally tracked me down
after all these years.

485
00:41:04.709 --> 00:41:06.935
Lucas:
<i>Who are you?</i>

486
00:41:06.959 --> 00:41:08.976
My name is Dalton.

487
00:41:09.000 --> 00:41:11.976
- Are you military?
- I was.

488
00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:16.101
But now I recruit
men like you.

489
00:41:16.125 --> 00:41:20.476
I develop them
for an elite unit.

490
00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:22.976
What unit?

491
00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:24.476
What branch?

492
00:41:24.500 --> 00:41:27.001
Exactly.

493
00:41:28.166 --> 00:41:30.834
So...

494
00:41:32.208 --> 00:41:33.768
this is revenge?

495
00:41:33.792 --> 00:41:36.601
Revenge?

496
00:41:36.625 --> 00:41:37.518
Not really.

497
00:41:37.542 --> 00:41:41.875
- ( gunshot )
- ( screams )

498
00:41:44.959 --> 00:41:46.583
Where's Job?

499
00:41:46.625 --> 00:41:48.559
How the fuck
would I know?

500
00:41:48.583 --> 00:41:51.142
No. no. no. no.
You know how this works.

501
00:41:51.166 --> 00:41:52.685
You taught me.

